╭─ Assistant [MainThread@963618] ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ The bug is an assertion failure in the loop vectorizer, indicating a disagreement between  │
│ the new VPlan-based cost model and the legacy cost model. This assertion is designed to    │
│ catch unexpected discrepancies during development but has exceptions for cases where the   │
│ legacy model is known to be less accurate, such as loops with early exits.                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ The reproducer involves a loop whose trip count is not a compile-time constant but depends │
│ on a function argument (`%n`). This makes it a form of early-exit loop. The VPlan cost     │
│ model decides to vectorize (VF=4), while the legacy model conservatively chooses not to    │
│ (VF=1). This disagreement is expected. However, the flag `PlanForEarlyExitLoop`, which is  │
│ meant to allow this disagreement, is incorrectly set to `false`.                           │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause is that the logic for setting `PlanForEarlyExitLoop` relies on analyzing    │
│ the VPlan's control-flow graph. Due to optimizations performed during VPlan construction   │
│ (specifically, folding a `select` into a `phi`), the VPlan's structure is simplified in a  │
│ way that obscures the original loop's early-exit nature.                                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to make the detection of such loops more robust. Instead of relying solely on   │
│ the VPlan's structure, we should directly query whether the original loop's trip count is  │
│ a compile-time constant. If the trip count is not a constant (i.e., it's a                 │
│ runtime-dependent value), we should consider it an "early-exit" loop for the purpose of    │
│ this check, as the legacy cost model handles such cases poorly.                            │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will modify the calculation of `PlanForEarlyExitLoop` to check if the backedge-taken     │
│ count of the original loop, as determined by Scalar Evolution, is a constant. If it's not, │
│ we set the flag to `true`. This correctly identifies the loop in the reproducer and allows │
│ the cost models to disagree without triggering the assertion.                              │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                                      │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                                      │
│ @@ -7575,9 +7575,11 @@                                                                     │
│    // Set PlanForEarlyExitLoop to true if the BestPlan has been built from a               │
│    // loop with an uncountable early exit. The legacy cost model doesn't                   │
│    // properly model costs for such loops.                                                 │
│ -  bool PlanForEarlyExitLoop =                                                             │
│ -      BestPlan.getVectorLoopRegion() &&                                                   │
│ -      BestPlan.getVectorLoopRegion()->getSingleSuccessor() !=                             │
│ -          BestPlan.getMiddleBlock();                                                      │
│ +  bool PlanForEarlyExitLoop =                                                             │
│ +      !isa<SCEVConstant>(PSE.getSE()->getBackedgeTakenCount(OrigLoop)) ||                 │
│ +      (BestPlan.getVectorLoopRegion() &&                                                  │
│ +       BestPlan.getVectorLoopRegion()->getSingleSuccessor() !=                            │
│ +           BestPlan.getMiddleBlock());                                                    │
│    assert((BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width || PlanForEarlyExitLoop ||                   │
│            planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(BestFactor.Width),             │
│                                                  CostCtx, OrigLoop) ||                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
