│ The root cause of the bug is an assertion failure indicating a disagreement between the    │
│ VPlan and legacy cost models in the loop vectorizer. This happens for a loop with a        │
│ runtime-dependent trip count. The assertion is designed to allow such disagreements for    │
│ "early-exit" loops, but the flag `PlanForEarlyExitLoop` is incorrectly set to `false`      │
│ because VPlan optimizations obscure the loop's early-exit nature from a purely structural  │
│ check.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ My previous attempts to fix this by using methods from `LoopVectorizationLegality` or      │
│ `ScalarEvolution` either failed to compile or caused other test failures, indicating they  │
│ were not the correct or most robust way to identify this specific condition.               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The most direct way to determine if a loop has a variable trip count (and thus should be   │
│ treated as an "early-exit" loop for this assertion's purpose) is to check if the           │
│ backedge-taken count provided by Scalar Evolution is a compile-time constant. If it's not  │
│ a constant, the legacy cost model is known to be less reliable, and a disagreement with    │
│ the VPlan model should be permitted.                                                       │
│                                                                                            │
│ I will implement this by changing the condition for `PlanForEarlyExitLoop`. Instead of     │
│ relying on the VPlan's structure or other legality checks, I will directly check if the    │
│ loop's backedge-taken count is a `SCEVConstant`. This is a precise and robust way to       │
│ identify the loops that cause this problem.                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                                      │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                                      │
│ @@ -7575,9 +7575,11 @@                                                                     │
│    // Set PlanForEarlyExitLoop to true if the BestPlan has been built from a               │
│    // loop with an uncountable early exit. The legacy cost model doesn't                   │
│    // properly model costs for such loops.                                                 │
│ -  bool PlanForEarlyExitLoop =                                                             │
│ -      BestPlan.getVectorLoopRegion() &&                                                   │
│ -      BestPlan.getVectorLoopRegion()->getSingleSuccessor() !=                             │
│ -          BestPlan.getMiddleBlock();                                                      │
│ +  bool PlanForEarlyExitLoop = !isa<SCEVConstant>(                                         │
│ +                                  PSE.getSE()->getBackedgeTakenCount(OrigLoop)) ||        │
│ +                              (BestPlan.getVectorLoopRegion() &&                          │
│ +                               BestPlan.getVectorLoopRegion()->getSingleSuccessor() !=    │
│ +                                   BestPlan.getMiddleBlock());                            │
│    assert((BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width || PlanForEarlyExitLoop ||                   │
│            planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(BestFactor.Width),             │
│                                                  CostCtx, OrigLoop) ||                     │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
