│ The bug is an assertion failure in the loop vectorizer, caused by a disagreement between   │
│ the new VPlan-based cost model and the legacy cost model. This assertion is intended to    │
│ catch unexpected discrepancies but has an exception for loops with early exits, where the  │
│ legacy model is known to be less accurate.                                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ The reproducer features a loop with a runtime-dependent trip count, which qualifies as an  │
│ early-exit loop. The VPlan model chooses to vectorize (VF=4), while the legacy model       │
│ conservatively does not (VF=1). This disagreement should be allowed, but the               │
│ `PlanForEarlyExitLoop` flag, which controls this, is incorrectly set to `false`. This is   │
│ because optimizations during VPlan construction alter its control-flow graph, making the   │
│ structural check for an early exit fail.                                                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to make the detection of such loops more robust. Instead of relying solely on   │
│ the VPlan's structure, we should directly consult the `LoopVectorizationLegality`          │
│ analysis, which has already determined if the original loop has an "uncountable" early     │
│ exit (i.e., one with a non-constant trip count). By adding                                 │
│ `Legal->hasUncountableEarlyExit()` to the condition, we correctly identify the loop in the │
│ reproducer, allowing the cost models to disagree without triggering the assertion. This    │
│ resolves the crash while correctly handling the nuances of different loop types.           │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```patch                                                                                   │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                                      │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                                      │
│ @@ -7575,9 +7575,10                                                                        │
